<h1><a href="../">Perl Advent Calendar 2010-12</a>-04</h1>
<h2 align="center">Debuggin' blinken strings</h2>
<h3 align="center">by Jerrad Pierce</h3>
<p>Today we bring you a humble stocking stuffer, <tt><a href="http://search.cpan.org/perldoc?Devel::Eval">Devel::Eval</a></tt>. A module which permits you to step through <tt><span class="k">eval</span></tt>uated strings as you might any other code. Unfortunately <tt><span class="k">eval</span></tt> is one of the core functions that cannot be overridden, so to access this functionality you must change your calls from <tt><span class="k">eval</span></tt> to <tt><span class="w">dval</span></tt>&mdash;which might lead you to try to <tt><span class="k">use</span></tt> <tt>Devel::Dval</tt> instead&mdash; after explicitly importing the subroutine.</p>
